        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-05-15T17:14:35Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDate>2017-11-07</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Independence from Credit Policy Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill limits the types of securities that the Federal Reserve Board (FRB) may acquire&nbsp;in the open market&nbsp;to: (1)&nbsp;gold stock; (2) currency; and (3) direct obligations of the United States, foreign banks, or&nbsp;the International Monetary Fund. The FRB must exchange all other assets with the Department of the Treasury for direct U.S. obligations of equivalent value. </p>]]></text>
